# Cardinal IG Roanoke — Maintenance Dashboard

A single-file maintenance KPI dashboard for Cardinal IG Roanoke, built for the Maintenance Planning & Scheduling team. Designed to run as a static GitHub Pages site — no server, no build process, no dependencies to install.

---

## Live Site

> `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/`

To set up GitHub Pages: **Settings → Pages → Branch: main → Folder: / (root) → Save**

The file must be named `index.html` in the root of the repo for GitHub Pages to serve it at the root URL.

---

## What's on the Dashboard

### KPI Dashboard
The main page. Everything fits on one screen — no scrolling.

- **Top 10 Downtime Ticker** — Scrolling ticker at the top showing January and February's top 10 breakdown equipment by downtime hours and repair count
- **Plant Overview** — Side-by-side Jan vs Feb stats for Work Orders, Planned Work Rate, Breakdown %, and Total Labor hours with trend arrows (green = improving, red = trending bad)
- **Labor Hour Mix** — Stacked bar showing PM vs Breakdown vs Other hours for each month
- **35% BD Target Tracker** — Visual goal bar showing whether breakdown hours stayed under the 35% threshold
- **Priority Alerts** — Flagged equipment issues (new problems and repeat offenders)
- **IG Line Health Cards** — Summary cards for IG1–IG4 with MTBF and avg repair time
- **Line Reliability Bars** — Horizontal bar chart comparing MTBF across all four lines
- **Equipment Repair Detail** — 2×2 grid of breakdown tables for each IG line (equipment, repair count, avg time between failures, avg repair time with color-coded severity badges)

### Shift Performance
A separate page showing labor breakdown by shift (A/B/C/D/Day).

- YTD labor totals per shift
- Jan and Feb hours per shift
- Tech count per shift
- Scrolling **Updates Ticker** — color-coded badges for newly added PMs, KPI trends, and priority alerts

---

## Header Features (always visible)

- **Cardinal IG logo** and facility name
- **Shift indicators** — A/B/C/D tabs showing crew names, highlights the active shift
- **Live clock** — Updates every second
- **Live weather** — Current conditions for Vinton, VA via Open-Meteo API (temperature, condition, wind speed)

---

## Data Source

All data is sourced from **PMWare CMMS** labor reports exported for:
- January 2026 (01/01–01/31)
- February 2026 (01/01–02/20, partial month)

Data is hardcoded into the HTML. To update for a new month, pull a fresh labor report from PMWare and update the relevant values in the file.

